description.narrative: UNICEF and MoSD as lead of the social sector, introduced the innovative real-time monitoring platform (RapidPro) to serve as a channel of communication for families with children with disabilities and the respective service providers. In addition, community mobilization services to increase the awareness of families and communities on the needs of young children and mothers on health, nutrition, WASH and development were achieved resulting in the enhancement of care givers knowledge and practices toward addressing the needs of their children. Especially those with disabilities and or developmental delays. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:20/01/2020
